  , issueCommentBody =
      "I have found a workaround for this issue. Instead of using fromtimestamp, we generate a unix epoch date:\r\n`epoch = datetime.datetime(1970, 1, 1, tzinfo=RqlTzinfo(obj['timezone']))`\r\nand then offset it by the epoch_time\r\n`epoch += datetime.timedelta(0, 0, 0, obj['epoch_time'])`\r\nand return that. Without timezone is the same minus the tzinfo param.\r\nTested, and results are as expected."
